Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.19,0:01:28.10,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:86190,88109}The bus back goes\Nin 2 hours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.10,0:01:31.15,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:88109,91154}Yes. It will be the last,\Nso make sure not to miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.15,0:01:34.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:91154,94240}To reach the town,\Ngo straight down the road…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.24,0:01:35.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:94240,95992}Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.99,0:01:37.74,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:95992,97744}I know that very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.66,0:01:49.63,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:106669,109631}I never thought\NI'd miss this place so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:52.80,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:110590,112800}My hometown.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:56.63,lassie episode,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:111716,116638}{\blur0.5\fad(300,0)\pos(320,300)}I Want To See\NMy Grandmother
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:02.51,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:119682,122518}Don't be a clown.\NWhat do you want after all these years?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:07.02,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:122518,127023}I'm saying, I apologize.\NLet's forget the past and live together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.27,0:02:09.73,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:128274,129734}Get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.19,0:02:12.52,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:130193,132528}I don't want to see your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.83,0:02:25.37,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:142830,145375}Uh, Grandma Forrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.37,0:02:28.12,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:145375,148127}What is it, John Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.12,0:02:30.92,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:148127,150922}Mr. Curry kept you\Nafter school today again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.92,0:02:32.09,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:150922,152090}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.09,0:02:35.76,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:152090,155760}It's because you've been\Nreading books all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.76,0:02:38.13,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:155760,158137}It's no wonder you\Noverslept and were late.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:42.18,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:159055,162183}Grandma Forrest sees everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:46.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:162183,166145}Looking down from that window she knows\Neverything that happens around the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:48.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:166646,168147}You're late, John!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:49.77,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:168523,169774}I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.77,0:02:51.90,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:169774,171901}I saw something\Nvery strange just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:52.44,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:171901,172443}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:53.44,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:172443,173444}Very strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:54.52,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:173444,174529}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.52,0:02:57.65,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:174529,177657}I never saw Grandma Forrest\Nact like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.65,0:02:59.82,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:177657,179826}She was very angry with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.82,0:03:00.61,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:179826,180618}Angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:02.41,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:180618,182412}Our Grandma Forrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.41,0:03:03.41,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:182412,183413}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.78,0:03:06.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:183788,186040}She poured water on him\Nfrom the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.04,0:03:09.41,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:186040,189419}I must say, it was\Na remarkable welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.41,0:03:10.92,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:189419,190920}It was to be expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.92,0:03:13.67,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:190920,193673}You ran away from home\Ntwenty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:16.92,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:193673,196926}You didn't try to contact her, not even once.\NYou can only blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.92,0:03:18.72,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:196926,198720}Thank you for the towel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.72,0:03:19.59,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:198720,199595}Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:22.43,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:200805,202432}Twenty years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.43,0:03:25.47,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:202432,205476}For me, it flew by\Nin a blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:28.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:205476,208896}It never occurred to me that Pops\Ncould have died in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.89,0:03:30.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:208896,210148}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:34.15,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:210148,214152}I do not think a good-for-nothing son\Nlike myself can be easily forgiven.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.15,0:03:35.36,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:214152,215361}Are you going back already?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:38.90,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:215361,218906}Yes. I absolutely have\Nto go back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:42.61,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:218906,222618}I plan to visit her frequently,\Nfor as long as time allows.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:46.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:223411,226998}I will stay patient and hope\Nthat she will forgive me, eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:47.66,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:226998,227665}See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.66,0:03:48.62,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:227665,228624}Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:50.29,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:229584,230293}Son?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.17,0:03:53.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:232170,233045}Sir…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:03:56.96,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:233379,236966}Who is that man? I saw him\Nin front of Grandma Forrest's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.96,0:03:57.55,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:236966,237550}Well…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.09,0:03:59.55,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:238092,239552}He is Ms. Forrest's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.80,0:04:02.09,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:240803,242096}Grandma Forrest's?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:03.18,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:242096,243181}Her son?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:03.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:243181,243890}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.89,0:04:08.10,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:243890,248102}But Grandma Forrest said\Nshe didn't want to see his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.10,0:04:14.06,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:248102,254066}Albert left this town after having\Na huge fight with his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.06,0:04:15.15,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:254066,255151}A huge fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:49.10,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:287809,289101}Rejected again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.68,0:04:53.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:289685,293314}Why doesn't\NGrandma Forrest let him in?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:54.85,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293314,294857}He's her son, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.85,0:04:56.23,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:294857,296234}I don't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:58.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:296234,298319}Something happened\Nbetween those two a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.31,0:05:00.94,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298319,300947}I don't really know\Nwhat it was about, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.94,0:05:05.49,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:300947,305493}Her son left town\Nbefore our family settled here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:11.29,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305493,311290}No matter what happened, I'm sure\Nthat deep down she wants to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.29,0:05:11.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:311290,311999}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.99,0:05:13.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:311999,313084}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:14.41,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:313084,314418}Am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.41,0:05:16.50,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:314418,316504}Isn't that what family is all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.50,0:05:18.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316504,318256}Yes. Very true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.25,0:05:22.71,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:318256,322718}John, you are right, of course.\NBut you don't know their circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:26.22,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:322718,326222}If I was a parent, I'd want\Nto see my children, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.22,0:05:27.72,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:326222,327723}Same goes for you, right, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.10,0:05:30.22,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:329100,330226}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.22,0:05:31.56,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:330226,331561}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.64,0:05:33.72,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:332645,333729}My goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:36.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:334146,336899}Oh, where are you headed\Non your day off?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.65,0:05:41.69,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:337650,341696}I'm going to talk for a bit\Nwith Mrs. Forrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.61,0:05:52.16,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348619,352164}What does he mean,\N"live together"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:352456,354250}That shameless scamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:56.16,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:354250,356168}Mrs. Forrest.\NDo you have a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.46,0:05:59.88,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357461,359881}Who do we have here?\NSam Carraclough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.88,0:06:01.13,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:359881,361132}When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.13,0:06:02.42,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:361132,362425}Oh, please, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:06.47,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362425,366470}How could a hawk like you\Nmiss anything that happens outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.72,0:06:10.18,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:367722,370182}Can I come in for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.56,0:06:16.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:375563,376898}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.89,0:06:19.27,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376898,379275}It's for you to open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.27,0:06:23.44,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:379275,383446}A strange man is bothering me lately,\Nso I began to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:27.45,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:385197,387450}Why would you go that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:31.53,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:387950,391537}Isn't that strange man\Nactually your son?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.53,0:06:32.87,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:391537,392872}My son, you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.87,0:06:33.66,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:392872,393664}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:35.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393664,395082}Sam Carraclough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:35.75,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395082,395750}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.75,0:06:39.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395750,399045}I don't have a son!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.04,0:06:42.63,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:399045,402632}My only family is\Nmy late husband George!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.63,0:06:45.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:402632,405259}What? I mean…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.25,0:06:46.42,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:405259,406427}Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:50.18,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:407511,410181}I'm telling you.\NI don't have any children—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.76,0:06:54.22,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:412767,414226}Good Lord!\NMrs. Forrest!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:57.10,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:415269,417104}D… Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.10,0:06:59.77,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:417104,419774}John, call Dr. Hopper.\NQuickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:01.56,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:419774,421567}Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.90,0:07:10.82,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:427907,430826}It was just a mild hypertension.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.28,0:07:15.33,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:431285,435331}At your age, you should\Nbe careful not to get too upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:18.83,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:437458,438834}I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.25,0:07:20.37,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:439251,440378}How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.37,0:07:21.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:440378,441087}Eh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.08,0:07:23.21,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:441087,443214}Will Grandma come soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:28.42,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:443214,448427}Oh? No, she still holds\Na grudge against me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:31.09,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:448427,451097}I can't do much about it.\NShe's stubborn like a mule.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:32.34,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:451097,452348}Is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:39.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452723,459146}When I look at this picture,\Nshe looks like a very nice grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:43.10,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:459522,463109}I made you dinner.\NI'll leave it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:44.73,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:463109,464735}John Carraclough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.11,0:07:48.40,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:465111,468406}There is no need to treat me\Nlike I was a patient in a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:51.49,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:468406,471492}Aren't you going to be late\Nfor kite flying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.74,0:07:52.57,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:471742,472576}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.57,0:07:54.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:472576,474996}Did I tell you about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.99,0:07:57.95,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:474996,477957}My eyes are sharp as ever.\NI see everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.95,0:07:59.20,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:477957,479208}You can go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:08:00.54,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:479208,480543}Okay. See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.50,0:08:07.00,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:483504,487008}Aren't you going with him, Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.01,0:08:14.18,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489010,494181}I've been watching over this town\Nfor quite a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:15.51,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:494515,495516}Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.51,0:08:17.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:495516,497893}Dohan is passing by, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:23.94,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:498310,503941}He's worrying over something again.\NCompletely unduly, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:26.73,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:504191,506736}You were raised\Nin Sam Carraclough's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.73,0:08:30.19,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:506736,510197}I still remember the first day\Nwe met in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:33.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:510197,513242}He was still wet behind ears\Nand went to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.24,0:08:37.49,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:513242,517496}The day John took you in\Nseems like yesterday to me, Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.04,0:08:43.29,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:522043,523294}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.29,0:08:44.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:523294,524045}This?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.04,0:08:47.33,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524045,527339}It's an old picture of my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.96,0:08:49.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:527965,529258}This is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.25,0:08:52.92,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:529258,532928}That's my late husband George.\NAnd this pumpkin here…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:56.84,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534013,536849}He was such a nice kid back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.47,0:09:04.27,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:538476,544273}At some point, he went down the wrong path.\NWhere did I make a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.27,0:09:08.86,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:544273,548861}He wrote a note that he wanted to seek\Nfreedom in a foreign country and left us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.69,0:09:14.20,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:549695,554200}George worked like crazy to\Nmake money for our son's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.20,0:09:18.37,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:554200,558370}He used some of it to buy an ancient gold piece,\Nand looked forward to passing it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:22.37,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:558370,562374}But that boy stole the gold piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:24.16,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:562666,564168}Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:26.87,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:564168,566879}I didn't know what he was doing\Nand where he lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.87,0:09:30.38,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:566879,570382}He never came back,\Neven when his father died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:36.88,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570674,576889}And now he has the nerve to come\Nand ask me to live with him in some city.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.22,0:09:39.60,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:578224,579600}Who does he think he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:41.60,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:580309,581602}That ungrateful scoundrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.56,0:09:48.56,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:587566,588567}Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:50.56,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:588734,590569}It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.65,0:09:53.53,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:591654,593531}You're late, Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.53,0:09:56.07,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:593531,596075}Were you at Grandma Forrest's\Nall that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.11,0:09:58.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:597118,598994}At Grandma Forrest's?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:02.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598994,602081}Huh? Lassie, did you\Nbecome friends with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.17,0:10:09.54,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:608170,609547}What's up, Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.54,0:10:12.21,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:609547,612216}Ah, look!\NSomeone is down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.21,0:10:13.84,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:612216,613843}What are they doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:18.55,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:617304,618556}Excuse us…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.09,0:10:19.97,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:619098,619974}Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:21.30,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:619974,621308}Are you feeling well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:23.35,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:621308,623352}Am I feeling…?\NYou got it wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.35,0:10:28.06,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:623352,628065}I lost something precious around here,\Nand I'm looking for it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.06,0:10:29.48,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:628065,629483}Something precious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.48,0:10:32.86,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:629483,632862}It's a necklace I got from my Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:34.53,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:632862,634530}A necklace?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.53,0:10:37.65,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:634530,637658}It was very precious to my Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:42.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:641120,642997}Ah! There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.99,0:10:45.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:642997,645040}I'm so happy. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.04,0:10:47.79,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:645040,647793}By the way, I don't think\NI've seen you around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.79,0:10:49.42,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:647793,649420}Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.42,0:10:51.63,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649420,651630}I'm Roy George Forrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.63,0:10:52.67,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:651630,652673}Forrest?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:55.46,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:652673,655467}Oh, could you be…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.46,0:10:57.51,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655467,657511}Grandma Forrest's grandson?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.51,0:10:58.42,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:657511,658429}Hm?
Comment: 0,0:11:01.47,0:11:01.47,[chapter],[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:661473,661473}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.89,0:11:06.39,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:663893,666395}Do you know my grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.39,0:11:08.35,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:666395,668355}Well, duh! Everyone knows her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.35,0:11:14.36,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:668355,674361}Yeah. But come to think of it,\Nshe knows everything about us,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.36,0:11:18.65,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:674361,678657}whereas we don't actually know\Nthe first thing about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:19.57,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:678657,679575}Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:21.11,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679575,681118}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:24.83,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:681118,684830}I also don't know her,\Neven though she's my grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:25.58,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:684830,685581}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.62,0:11:29.46,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:686624,689460}If you don't know anything\Nabout your grandma,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.46,0:11:32.58,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:689460,692588}she has the opinion of being\Nvery harsh and stubborn—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:33.54,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:692588,693547}Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.54,0:11:35.54,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:693547,695549}Knock it off.\NYou're being rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:37.80,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:695549,697801}Ah, right. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.88,0:11:43.80,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:698886,703807}It's okay! My Dad said Grandma\Nwas harsh and stubborn as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:48.97,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:703807,708979}That's why even if when I asked to take me\Nto her place with him, he wouldn't let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.48,0:11:53.02,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:709480,713025}We have an old picture\Nof Grandma at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:55.81,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:713025,715819}She looks very kind\Nand has a nice smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.27,0:12:01.45,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:717279,721450}Every time I look at that photo,\NI wish I could meet Grandma in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.11,0:12:03.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:722117,723244}That's why…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:04.07,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:723244,724078}That's why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.07,0:12:09.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:725079,729250}That's why I finally came here\Nwithout telling my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.25,0:12:10.66,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:729250,730668}All by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.33,0:12:14.83,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:733337,734838}Let's go see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.83,0:12:16.96,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:734838,736966}I'll guide you to her place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.96,0:12:17.84,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:736966,737841}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.34,0:12:26.76,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:745349,746767}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.76,0:12:29.77,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:746767,749770}My wife and my son\Nwant to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.77,0:12:31.98,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749770,751981}It's your grandson, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:34.60,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:751981,754608}You want to see him, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:36.61,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:755109,756610}My grandson, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:40.78,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:756610,760781}My only family\Nis my late husband George.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.78,0:12:42.61,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:760781,762616}I don't have any children.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.61,0:12:45.91,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762616,765911}If I have no children, it means\NI have no grandchildren either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.91,0:12:48.91,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:765911,768914}Why would I want\Nto meet some strangers?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:50.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:768914,770082}But, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:51.33,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:770082,771333}Go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.33,0:12:54.12,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771333,774128}If you don't,\NI will pour more water on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.67,0:13:03.63,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:780676,783637}Grandma doesn't want to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:05.13,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:783637,785139}That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:06.05,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:785139,786056}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:06.72,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:786056,786724}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.30,0:13:10.47,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:787308,790477}Of course she wants to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.47,0:13:15.23,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:790477,795232}She's just unable to say it out loud,\Nbecause she doesn't want to give in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:16.23,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795232,796233}Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.60,0:13:18.77,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:796608,798777}Is there anything we could do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.77,0:13:19.73,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:798777,799737}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.73,0:13:21.11,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:799737,801113}Any ideas, John?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.11,0:13:23.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:801113,803240}Hmm. Let me think.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.69,0:13:26.95,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:803699,806952}I can't believe she's this stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:29.91,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:806952,809913}What is it?\NDo you give up already?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.91,0:13:31.29,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:809913,811290}Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:37.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:811290,817254}Since I left this town, I went to many places\Nand finally managed to build a successful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.04,0:13:41.05,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:818047,821050}I found a place for myself\Nand settled down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.05,0:13:45.26,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:821050,825262}I recently realized that\Nthe only missing piece is my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.67,0:13:48.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:825679,828140}It took me only\Ntwenty years to realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:49.05,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828140,829058}Twenty years!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.55,0:13:50.55,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:829558,830559}I… I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.06,0:13:55.10,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:831060,835105}That's why I'm not going\Nto give up so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:14:00.98,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:835105,840986}That's the spirit. You just have to be\Neven more stubborn than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.98,0:14:02.15,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:840986,842154}Amen to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:04.82,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:842154,844823}Maybe I take after my Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:07.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:845491,847242}A grandson?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.45,0:14:08.16,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:847451,848160}Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:09.49,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:848744,849495}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.03,0:14:12.62,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:850037,852623}What brings you to my home,\NJohn Carraclough?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.95,0:14:18.50,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:854958,858504}I brought some cookies with me.\NI thought maybe we could have tea, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.96,0:14:21.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:858962,861256}I smell something fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.25,0:14:23.25,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:861256,863258}Whatever. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:30.43,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:865761,870432}My cousin came by today.\NIs it okay if he tags along?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.97,0:14:32.93,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:871975,872935}That child…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:36.43,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:873394,876438}Albert? No. It's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:41.52,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:879858,881527}Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:43.94,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881527,883946}Remember, I'm not here\Nas her grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.94,0:14:46.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:883946,886240}If she finds out, she'll drive us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.24,0:14:47.53,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:886240,887533}Everything will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:52.41,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:889952,892413}It's nice to drink tea together\Nfrom time to time, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.95,0:14:55.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:894957,895999}{\i1}Grandma…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.12,0:15:00.00,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:897126,900003}I believe you said he was your cousin,\NJohn Carraclough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:02.50,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:900003,902506}But I can't say\Nhe looks anything like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.50,0:15:06.17,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:902506,906176}Really? Well, he just happened\Nto come to my house today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.17,0:15:06.88,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:906176,906885}Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.88,0:15:10.09,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:906885,910097}I didn't know you had a cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.09,0:15:12.18,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:910097,912182}Really? But there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:14.01,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:912182,914017}John!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:14.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:914017,914893}John?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:17.06,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:914893,917062}Are you there?\NIf you're not, tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.39,0:15:19.56,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:917396,919565}They're calling you,\NJohn Carraclough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:21.35,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919565,921358}Go on and answer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.44,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:921358,923444}Okay. I'll leave you for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.44,0:15:26.28,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:923444,926280}Roy, pour some tea for Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.28,0:15:27.19,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:926280,927197}Oh… Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:28.57,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:927573,928574}Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:31.20,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:928866,931201}I can't. Sandy's calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.20,0:15:32.57,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931201,932578}See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:38.12,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:936290,938125}You'd better go with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:40.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:938125,940043}No. I'll prepare the tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.21,0:15:44.96,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:944214,944965}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.84,0:15:51.05,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:948844,951054}Why are you standing like a pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.38,0:15:54.55,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:951388,954558}We're having tea,\Nso bring a chair and take a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:56.51,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:954558,956518}Ah… Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.15,0:16:05.94,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:964151,965944}What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.94,0:16:07.65,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:965944,967654}My name is Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.94,0:16:09.90,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:968947,969907}Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.40,0:16:15.87,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971408,975871}Hmph. That's one funny name\Nyour parents gave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.70,0:16:22.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978707,982044}This town…\NThis town produces coal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:22.83,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:982044,982836}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.21,0:16:26.34,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983212,986340}My Grandpa was a worker\Nin a coal mine, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.92,0:16:28.55,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986924,988550}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.55,0:16:29.92,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:988550,989927}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:31.59,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:989927,991595}My husband was one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.42,0:16:34.26,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:992429,994264}He was working in a mine as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.26,0:16:35.68,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:994264,995682}What a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.68,0:16:38.60,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:995682,998602}He was a very proud man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.60,0:16:40.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:998602,1000312}But…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.31,0:16:42.64,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1000312,1002648}But? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:49.36,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004107,1009363}So your father inherited\Nyour grandfather's ambition
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.36,0:16:52.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1009363,1012991}and became\Na great miner as well, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:54.95,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1014201,1014952}Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.95,0:16:58.37,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1014952,1018372}Oh, I was wrong? That's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.46,0:17:04.46,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1023460,1024461}Ma'am…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.46,0:17:05.50,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1024461,1025504}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.50,0:17:08.59,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1025504,1028590}Before I was born,\Nmy Dad was a sailor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.59,0:17:11.13,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1028590,1031134}He visited many, many countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:14.01,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1031134,1034012}He always yearned\Nfor that kind of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.01,0:17:16.05,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034012,1036056}To your detriment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:17.09,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1036056,1037099}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.09,0:17:20.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1037099,1040310}I do not want to talk\Nabout this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.56,0:17:29.77,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1046567,1049778}She's not looking.\NNow's the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.45,0:17:40.45,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1058453,1060455}I can't hear anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.45,0:17:43.62,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060455,1063625}They're not talking at all, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.04,0:17:46.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1064042,1066086}Listen, Colin…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.12,0:17:48.63,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1067129,1068630}Okay. Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.75,0:17:53.71,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1069756,1073719}Isn't it time for you to go,\NJohn's cousin?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.71,0:17:54.46,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073719,1074469}It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.88,0:17:59.64,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1077889,1079641}Good bye, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.10,0:18:00.80,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1080100,1080809}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.14,0:18:08.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1086148,1088317}Oh, no! Don't do this, I have to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:11.65,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1090027,1091653}Lassie, let the boy go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.32,0:18:16.49,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095324,1096491}T-This is…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:19.87,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1097242,1099870}Show it to me, Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.78,0:18:22.12,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1100787,1102122}This is…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.37,0:18:24.75,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1102372,1104750}I got it from my Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.75,0:18:28.79,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1104750,1108795}It's a real… It's a gold piece that\Ndates back to the fifteenth century!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.79,0:18:30.88,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1108795,1110881}Could this be…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.09,0:18:36.59,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1113091,1116595}Do you know how many of George's\Nsalaries went into this thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.59,0:18:39.80,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1116595,1119806}What kind of a parent would\Nlet a child like you have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.80,0:18:43.01,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1119806,1123018}I don't know anything about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:46.48,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1123018,1126480}Dad never told me\Nanything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.48,0:18:52.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126480,1132319}He just told me that no matter how poor I get,\NI can never sell it for money.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:55.36,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133987,1135364}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:18:56.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135364,1136990}When my Dad was a sailor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.99,0:19:02.57,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136990,1142579}he was afflicted with bad illnesses,\Nhe was fired many times and suffered a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.82,0:19:03.78,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1142829,1143789}But…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.78,0:19:09.08,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1143789,1149086}{\fscx95}But no matter how difficult it got, he just grasped\Nthat coin tightly and told himself to do his best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:11.58,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1150462,1151588}Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:16.13,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1152464,1156134}So he never sold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.59,0:19:23.93,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1157594,1163934}I will never forget what he said to me\Nand will always strive to do my best with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.93,0:19:24.64,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1163934,1164643}Roy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.64,0:19:25.64,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1164643,1165644}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:29.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1165644,1169147}Don't just stand there.\NCome closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:32.52,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169856,1172526}I'm a bit old and\NI can't hear you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.52,0:19:34.94,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1172526,1174945}Come closer and talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.94,0:19:36.23,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1174945,1176238}I…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:39.24,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1176238,1179241}I'm so happy\Nthat I came to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.24,0:19:42.32,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1179241,1182327}My Dad didn't work in the mine\Nand became a sailor instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.32,0:19:43.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182327,1183995}yet I'm still very proud of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.49,0:19:48.12,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184496,1188125}That huge ship he worked on\Nwas powered by coal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.12,0:19:52.96,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1188125,1192963}It was coal that let the ship's furnace\Nheat and lead it to the seven seas!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.96,0:19:56.50,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192963,1196508}And it was my grandfather\Nwho mined that coal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:00.88,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1198468,1200887}I'm so glad that I came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:03.09,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1200887,1203098}And that I found Grandma\Nin this town…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.55,0:20:07.47,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1205559,1207477}Grandma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:08.97,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1207477,1208979}I knew that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.97,0:20:11.89,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1208979,1211898}Roy. That you…\Nare my grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.89,0:20:13.35,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1211898,1213358}Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.27,0:20:18.73,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216278,1218739}I know you're there,\NJohn Carraclough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:20.90,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218739,1220907}Show yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.90,0:20:22.53,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1220907,1222534}She does know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.90,0:20:25.12,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1222909,1225120}Call Albert for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.12,0:20:27.53,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1225120,1227539}But Dad went to\Nthe bus stop already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.53,0:20:30.37,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227539,1230375}He's still at Jones' store.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.37,0:20:34.04,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1230375,1234045}He wanted to be particularly\Npersistent today and didn't go home yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.04,0:20:38.17,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1234045,1238175}I always knew what he was up to,\Never since he was a little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.17,0:20:41.05,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1238175,1241052}Not this time, Grandma.\NThis time you missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:43.43,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1241386,1243430}Mr. Albert is already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.43,0:20:46.14,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1243430,1246141}He's been here for a while\Nand heard everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:52.31,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1248059,1252314}At last, for once you managed\Nto outwit me, John Carraclough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.73,0:20:54.06,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1252731,1254065}Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:57.23,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254065,1257235}I won't tell you to leave this town\Nand come live with me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.23,0:20:58.44,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1257235,1258445}So, please…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.44,0:21:01.28,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258445,1261281}I'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:06.20,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1263408,1266203}Welcome home, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.20,0:21:07.99,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266203,1267996}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.65,0:21:39.15,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1296650,1299152}Congratulations, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.78,0:21:44.36,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301780,1304366}Here it goes. Say cheese!
Comment: 0,0:21:58.71,0:21:58.71,[chapter],[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1318713,1318713}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.05,0:22:04.51,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1322050,1324511}{\i1}The mine has run out of coal!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.51,0:22:07.01,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324511,1327013}{\i1}If we don't do something,\Nit will get shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.01,0:22:10.80,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1327013,1330809}{\i1}Dad goes without sleep, trying\Nto figure out the cause and a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.80,0:22:12.43,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1330809,1332435}{\i1}I want to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:15.73,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332435,1335730}{\i1}Next episode:\N"John's Decision! Protect The Mine".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.73,0:22:17.19,lassie default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1335730,1337190}{\i1}Be sure to watch!
